article.headline: Winston-Salem 68, Norfolk St. 64
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Jamal Durham scored 16 points and grabbed 17 rebounds to help Winston-Salem State hold off Norfolk State 68-64 on Monday night, snapping a two-game skid. The Rams (8-18) held the Spartans to a season-low 23.3 percent shooting performance in the first half (7 of 30) as Michael Deloach, the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference's leading scorer, was 2-for-11 for seven points. Deloach finished with 25 points on 7-of-20 shooting from the field to surpass 1,000 career points for Norfolk State (8-17), which dropped its fourth straight game. Corey Lyons added 17 for the Spartans. Brian Fisher chipped in 10 points for Winston-Salem State, which shot 51.2 percent from the floor (22 of 43). The Rams led 27-8 in the first half and 32-19 at the break. The Spartans made it 57-52 with 2:56 left, but Winston-Salem State hit 10 of 15 free throws to seal the win.
